      "writtenOn": "2018-09-17T16:16:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i think we\u0027ve talked about this before. :-) i agree that it\u0027s confusing. i chose it to match autotest\u0027s current terminology (the \"client\" and \"server\" terms that we use for autotest tests, which i think are even more confusing since they reflect the test system\u0027s design, are deprecated, iirc).\n\nthe explanation that i gave last time, which i think you found reasonably satisfying, was that this describes where the test runs relative to the DUT -- local tests run on the DUT, while remote tests run separate from it.",
      "parentUuid": "94104caa_37476a1d",
      "revId": "713f326953534ea42cb89eddbbb2664bcf8751b7",
