      "writtenOn": "2018-09-17T16:16:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i couldn\u0027t come up with anything better (and i reject efforts to try to call tast tests \"tasts\", as it feels overly cutesy to me). :-P\n\nin practice, i think that the compiler makes it hard to be confused for too long about which one you\u0027re using. so far, the conflict has mostly just come up when i\u0027m writing unit tests for tast itself.",
      "parentUuid": "ef729b3f_2fcbfd8d",
